Description: FYPO is a formal ontology of phenotypes observed in fission yeast. FYPO is being developed to support the comprehensive and detailed representation of phenotypes in PomBase- the new online fission yeast resource (www.pombaes.org). Its scope is similar to that of the Ascomycete Phenotype Ontology (APO)- but FYPO includes more detailed pre-composed terms as well as computable definitions.
Authors: Name: BioPortal project on behalf of ontology owner.; Email:support@bioontology.org
